to actively participate, and that because it's repeated, and because it's a shared responsibility,

00:03:11.839 --> 00:03:16.600
both people need to do their part of it, no matter what role you're in, in an organization,

00:03:16.600 --> 00:03:20.919
one-on-ones give you the opportunity to practice your leadership skills.

00:03:20.919 --> 00:03:25.279
So it's really good to focus in on, it's regular, so it happens, and you can say, hey, how did

00:03:25.279 --> 00:03:29.839
that one go, learn over time, and you can exercise leadership muscles, again, from pretty

00:03:29.839 --> 00:03:35.320
much any position in a company or in an organization.

