All you have to do is take five minutes ahead of time to do a little bit of planning.

00:09:55.159 --> 00:09:58.479
It goes a really long way.

00:09:58.479 --> 00:10:05.960
So one last comment on team leads and team member one-on-ones, a lot of data teams I

00:10:05.960 --> 00:10:07.440
find are matrixed.

00:10:07.440 --> 00:10:08.440
So what do I mean by that?

00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:12.159
You have a data person, they're on a team with maybe a bunch of software developers

00:10:12.159 --> 00:10:17.080
or another skill set going on, and then they report, the data person reports up through

00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:20.780
a data chain, like a data management team and that kind of thing.

00:10:20.780 --> 00:10:24.599
If you have that situation, I just encourage you to spend a little extra time in that supportive

00:10:24.599 --> 00:10:28.359
mode and spend time talking about the goals of that team.

00:10:28.359 --> 00:10:31.179
If you're embedded and you have a specialty and you have a bunch of other people that

00:10:31.179 --> 00:10:35.320
don't have that same specialty, understanding what they're trying to achieve and tailoring

00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:37.760
your efforts to theirs is really important.

00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:41.440
Last thing is, if you're the manager on that other team, make sure you have the occasional

00:10:41.440 --> 00:10:44.520
one-on-one with the team lead that your person is in.

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:50.359
Again, talk about goals and how it's going, help them head off troubles if you can.

00:10:50.359 --> 00:10:54.000
So moving on to the next type of one-on-one.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:56.520
We have you and your boss.

00:10:56.520 --> 00:11:01.140
So for you and your boss, you're going to want to spend a little more time here prepping

00:11:01.140 --> 00:11:05.159
for it because frankly, what does boss mean?

00:11:05.159 --> 00:11:08.679
So we're assuming some level up or even a couple of levels up the hierarchy.

00:11:08.679 --> 00:11:11.599
Basically, each level up is going to add complexity.

00:11:11.599 --> 00:11:14.799
It's going to add more stuff that they're supposed to know about.

00:11:14.799 --> 00:11:20.119
And so you're going to help them by setting a little bit more context and being understanding

00:11:20.119 --> 00:11:21.520
about where they're coming from.

00:11:21.520 --> 00:11:27.080
I mean, basically, the wider your scope, the more things you don't know.

00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:29.799
And that's part of why managers often seem clueless.

00:11:29.799 --> 00:11:33.719
And I say that as a manager who has often seemed clueless.

00:11:33.719 --> 00:11:36.320
Wider scope, more likely not to know things.

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:37.359
That's just the nature of the beast.

00:11:37.359 --> 00:11:40.440
So when you're going into that, you're going to say, okay, I need to understand a little

00:11:40.440 --> 00:11:43.840
bit more about where my boss is coming from.

00:11:43.840 --> 00:11:47.239
And I'm going to try and tailor to that like, wow, they have a wider scope.

00:11:47.239 --> 00:11:50.679
I want to understand where they're coming from, tailor it to that, make it efficient

00:11:50.679 --> 00:11:54.719
for them to remember things and help them through that.

00:11:54.719 --> 00:11:58.219
Another goal we have is to really avoid meeting surprises.

00:11:58.219 --> 00:12:02.239
If they find out about something that's gone wrong on your team or something that wasn't

00:12:02.239 --> 00:12:06.239
delivered, but it's with meetings with some of their peers or those kind of things, you

00:12:06.239 --> 00:12:08.200
don't want them to find out from someone else.

00:12:08.200 --> 00:12:11.880
So one of your goals is always when you're looking at your topics, if you have something

00:12:11.880 --> 00:12:15.119
that they might hear about later, try and give them the heads up.

00:12:15.119 --> 00:12:20.359
That's going to go a long way to avoiding painful situations in conversations later.

00:12:20.359 --> 00:12:25.239
And then my last thought on this goal is just be explicit about what you're asking for from

00:12:25.239 --> 00:12:26.239
them.

00:12:26.239 --> 00:12:27.239
That'll help them give you the feedback.

00:12:27.239 --> 00:12:31.960
If you're saying, hey, this is just to inform you of what I'm doing or what's going on in

00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:35.640
the team or this thing about the project, say, informing.

00:12:35.640 --> 00:12:40.080
If it's more like, hey, I really want some advice about this, I don't know this or that,

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.840
ask for advice, be specific.

00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:44.719
The last thing is if you need an action for them, call it out.

00:12:44.719 --> 00:12:48.979
Ask, say, hey, I need your action, I need your help on this thing, get this funding,

00:12:48.979 --> 00:12:50.479
go to that other person, that kind of thing.

00:12:50.479 --> 00:12:55.000
So again, you're meeting with your boss, ask and categorize those different things.

